Operations in Afghanistan
Originally, the Air Force released the videos with the aim of recruiting soldiers, and as the Defense Ministry says, the contributions also serve the purpose of informing the population about the actual goals of the foreign operations.
This type of propaganda is almost free compared to conventional television commercials, according to defense expert Gordon Mackenzie to the BBC, but these videos always carry a certain amount of political message, as they confirm the existence of the military measures decided by the government in their own way.
Americans Advertise with Game
But the army also has to fight against amateur footage, which, in addition to the carefully edited, censored footage, also makes it into the network - such as those that show the death of the soldiers: in the somewhat hypocritical, "official" propaganda films, the losses are at most talked about, the bloody sides of the war are not, however.
By the way, numerous videos have already been uploaded to the platform from the war scenes in Iraq and Afghanistan, but the British have only recently discovered this "ghosting".
The Americans, however, advertise in a slightly different way, namely with the free downloadable shooting game "America's Army", in which the player can slip into the soldier's skin as part of a more or less lifelike simulation.
