Usually, the matter is settled with an apology.
Before getting caught up in embarrassing excuses, you should think about what you can really do to prepare your colleagues for unpleasant moments and try to consciously avoid these situations.
Borrowing something that doesn’t belong to you?
There’s hardly anything more nervous than grabbing a document, office supplies, or the phone, but it’s not there.
Yesterday the stapler was still on the desk - this morning it's gone?
Or is the lost ballpoint pen discovered on a colleague’s desk?
Without asking, you should not borrow anything from your colleagues, because they are rightly upset when they find that something has gone wrong.
So, don’t put envelopes or post-it from the office in your pocket, because it could hit you yourself: no more there if you need it urgently.
Discussing the privacy of your colleagues?
There is no effective way to stop a trap that has already been put into the world.
Who did what with whom?
Where and why?
The information (or assumptions) about the private life of colleagues should not be tied to everyone’s nose if possible!
And if someone opens up and reveals his inner secret to us, we should not abuse that trust!
It is best to be silent like a grave, rather than aligning the just present, even if others also know about the problems of the colleague.
Reported ill for no reason?
When you call the office to report yourself sick with agonizing headaches, because you just feel uncomfortable, or just want to rest, you should be clear about one thing: your own work, non-deferred accomplishments, projects with fixed deadlines now have to be done by your colleagues instead of yourself.
Don’t play badly for your colleagues!
If you already know the day before that you will not be able to get to the office the next day, or that something could happen, which is why you have to stay at home, you should report it in time so that neither the colleagues nor the boss are unexpectedly confronted with the absence.
Sum, Gekicher, Telephone
One is just deepened in his work, but is suddenly disturbed by the noisy gossip of the colleagues?
Did you hear a phone call that you shouldn’t have heard?
You should not annoy your colleagues with buzzing, singing, loud conversations (which you carry across their heads), trampling, constant scolding or nagging.
All of this can be very annoying, even if you are not exactly immersed in a task (writing, planning, organizing).
Is it always the fault of others?
If a project is not completed on time, you have forgotten to send an important letter or important messages, you should not look for the guilt of your own forgetfulness with others!
If possible, do not talk about the chaos in the office or the loud colleagues!
It is best to admit your mistakes and apologize if others have been affected!
The question of how to make up for the mistake, or how to make up for the missing, is just too appropriate!
In the office - a feeling like home?
Training pants and sleeping: Comfortable for at home, but has nothing to lose in the office!
Not even then should you dress so casually if the workplace would actually allow it!
Just do not get too slutty - you should respect both your colleagues and yourself to the point that you dress accordingly in the office - if desired, also pretty and elegant!
