Cuba also offers a marotte that is unique in the world and especially attracts railway enthusiasts.
The sugar cane from remote plantations brought steam and diesel-powered narrow lanes to the sugar factories.
Their fleet has not been renewed for decades, and so you can see clean and fully functioning locomotives, whose co-workers have been in the museum for a long time elsewhere.
Excursion destinations
