Government Debt to Rise to 1 Billion in 2009
Each Czech has a national debt of 84,000 kroner.
Total debt rose to SEK 842.7 billion by the end of September.
The government had planned to borrow 159.2 billion queens this year.
At the beginning of December, however, the Ministry reduced the plan to 152.8 billion thanks to the better development of the state budget policy.
The Czech Republic’s national debt rose to 842.7 billion kroner by the end of September.
In the first nine months of this year, they increased by 40.2 billion.
Since June, however, they have fallen by 13.4 billion.
The Ministry of Finance confirmed its information on the state debts from the beginning of October.
Each Czech has a debt of 84,000 kroner.
Over the entire past year, the state owed more than CZK 111 billion.
“Until now, it seems that thanks to the lower deficit for the coming year, we may not be able to cross the one-trillion-crore limit until 2009.
