Serbian President Boris Tradic, for his part, was of the opinion that a compromise should always be sought, and warned the Albanian majority from Kosovo of the consequences of a unilateral declaration of independence of the province.
Belgrade believes that it is particularly forcing a "domino effect" in a region that has been so much weakened by the independence wars of the 1990s.
