Nevertheless, Solbes noted in the halls of the Congress building that even if the current figure is not good, Spain’s inflation differential to the other members of the monetary union has remained more or less the same in recent years.
He also explained that there were fewer surprises in November than in the previous month, in which the government did not expect such a high increase.
We expected a value of around 4%, the Minister of Economics and Finance announced in terms of the forecast published today.
