Which insurance is best for me?
The car insurance, which covers a possible case of damage caused by the driver, includes a high cost, the amount of which again depends on various factors, such as age, gender, time of creation of the driver's license, family status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, it must be clear what we are dealing with here.
A car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurance policy holder.
This agreement shall be established in writing by means of an insurance contract which states that the Company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to provide the corresponding amount of compensation in the event of damages.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance that consists of several factors, including age, gender, time of issue of the driver's license, family status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that in the event of a higher risk of accident, higher contributions will also be due.
For this reason, both 25-year-olds and women have to pay less, because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of the companies, they tend to have fewer accidents as single persons.
The benefits assigned to the vehicle affect the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, the insurance companies must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to choose exactly the car insurance that best meets his personal needs.
We now list the most important points that should be taken into account when choosing an insurance in order to be able to make not only a performance, but also a price-oriented choice.
Those under 25 years of age encounter numerous obstacles when choosing a low-cost insurance, such as low driving practice and a young driver’s license.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to take out full cash insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full cash with self-insurance, so that the services of a full cash insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract involves the customer having to pay a part of the amount resulting from the damage himself.
The amount is determined prior to the conclusion of the contract and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher and lower the amount to be paid , explains Luis Noguera, Spain's chief representative at First Europa, an online insurance brokerage company.
Another option is the extended insurance that insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against damage to the car itself.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you’re under 25, it’s up to you to cut down on insurance costs; that’s how your credit rises by trying to drive cautiously and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate at the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in said tariffs.
The amount of credits and penalty payments depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can afford to increase the bonus payments, Noguera explains.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract. The reason for this is the fact that with increasing driving practice the accident rate drops.
Therefore, it is best to opt for full cash insurance with self-insurance.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the beginner's fear has been removed.
Nevertheless, for a married customer who does not have children, it is more advisable to take out full cash insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the person in question also allows it.
On the part of the insurers, couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and therefore their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, a full insurance with self-insurance (for an amount of 300 euros) would be the best option. In case you have received a high credit, it is recommended to use an extended insurance, which is not used until the third year of the vehicle.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to make a higher contribution payment, Luis Noguera notes.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a full cash insurance with self-employment (for an amount of around 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which is used only with a sufficiently high credit.
Ultimately, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it carries high costs that require a thorough selection that corresponds to our personal situation.
