They can even be of benefit to the card issuers.
The incentives for consumers to continue paying mortgage rates decrease when the real estate is less value than the value of the loan; as a result, card debt becomes more important among repayment priorities.
Card issuers can also respond much faster and more flexibly than lenders to the stormier conditions by changing interest rates or credit limits.
